abstract: the 14th arrondissement is a great arrondissement to live in BECAUSE of its tranquility. it has a few interesting spots and im very proud to have been living here my whole life hahah

You should have gone to the Cité Internationale Universitaire de Paris, It has a lot of interesting architecture, two building by Le Corbusier. I stayed there during my Erasmus exchange. There's also the illegal catacombs and Les Grands Voisins - it's like a community space in an abandoned hospital
Also, not sure if you know, but where you were pointing out the Petite Ceinture is one of the ways into the not legal catacombs... 👻👻
